title: Area Roundup: Newark volleyball wins senior night, unbeaten in conference
text:
Area Roundup: Newark volleyball wins senior night, unbeaten in conference Published: Tuesday, Oct. 13, 2015 10:34 p.m. CDT By: STAFF REPORTS 
NEWARK – The Newark volleyball team remained unbeaten in Little Ten Conference play Tuesday, scoring a 25-17, 28-26 win over Indian Creek on its senior night. Related Links Area Roundup: Newark volleyball wins senior night, unbeaten in conference 
The Lady Norse (20-5, 7-0), who also won the LTC Tournament, got eight kills, eight digs and two aces from Kelsea Zitt and eight kills and nine digs from Maddie Friestad. Megan DeClementi had a team-leading 23 digs, while Marissa Friestad had 20 assists. 
“This was a great way to celebrate our seniors tonight,” Newark coach Tonya Grayson said. “It was their last time to shine on their home floor, and they played well. Indian Creek fought hard, especially in Game 2, but we were able to keep our composure and finish the game.” 
CORRECTION 
Boys golf: In Tuesday’s edition of The Morris Daily Herald, Nick Bonomo was the Morris golfer that shot 89 at the Class 2A Nazareth Academy Sectional, not Jared Lines as was reported.
